<page api="js">
    <shortlink>ux component getConnectionType Method</shortlink>
    <topic parent="{dialog.object}" parentType="object" elementName="getConnectionType Method">{dialog.object}.getConnectionType Method</topic>

    <description>Returns the type of connection the device has. (May not return reliable information if not running in a Cordova shell).</description>
    <prototype>{dialog.Object}.getConnectionType()</prototype>
    <discussion>Possible return values are: 'none', 'connected_unknowntype', 'ethernet', 'wifi', '2g', '3g', '4g', and 'genericcell'.</discussion>
    <note>For Android be sure to include the 'Connection' or 'Network information' plugin.</note>
    
    <example code="js"><![CDATA[var connectionType = {dialog.Object}.getConnectionType();]]></example>
    
